# Rasm Prose Boundaries

Authority: `docs/standards/voice.md` (canonical). `.claude/skills/style-standards/references/voice.md` mirrors procedure for docgen edits.

## Reference-doc mode

- Write imperative facts with concrete nouns and active voice.
- Use `[CRITICAL]`, `[IMPORTANT]`, Dictum blocks, and bracket taxonomy only for durable constraints with enforcement value.
- Omit needless words; do not narrate file purpose or maintenance process.

## Banned in reference leaves

Applies to `docs/external-libs`, `docs/host`, `docs/host-libraries.md`, `docs/system-api-map`, `docs/testing-libs`, `docs/usage.md`, and similar capability docs:

- Routing strings: read CLAUDE, read AGENTS, read skills, validation gates, skill eval, agents should.
- Meta commentary: sourced from, this file catalogs, this file tells, transcript paths.
- Duplicated skill tables, quality command catalogs, or full manifest bodies.

## Exempt corpora

- `docs/standards/**` — instruction-shaped voice authority; agent-oriented markers are intentional.
- Manifest files matching this rule's globs (`AGENTS.md`, `CLAUDE.md`) — routing to leaves is allowed in manifest mode only.

## Manifest vs reference

| [INDEX] | [MODE]                                              | [ROUTE_CLAUDE] |     [STATE_LAW]     |
| :-----: | --------------------------------------------------- | :------------: | :-----------------: |
|   [1]   | Manifest (`AGENTS.md`, `CLAUDE.md`, `.mdc` routers) |      Yes       | Route only; distill |
|   [2]   | Reference leaf                                      |       No       |         Yes         |

## Chat and plan edits

When editing markdown outside manifests, apply reference-doc mode. Plans and review notes are not manifests unless they are checked-in `AGENTS.md` or `CLAUDE.md`.
